title: Super Bowl Matchup Worksheet
subtitle: Comprehensive statistical analysis for all matchups
description:
Detailed matchup statistics including team performance metrics, player stats, head-to-head records, and common opponent results.

CUMULATIVE EPA CHART:

The cumulative EPA chart displays Net EPA over the season for each team. Net EPA combines both offensive and defensive performance:

 • Net EPA = Offensive EPA - Defensive EPA Allowed

 • Offensive EPA: Total Expected Points Added by the offense (higher is better)

 • Defensive EPA Allowed: Total Expected Points Added by opposing offenses (lower is better for the defense)

 • Higher Net EPA indicates better overall team performance, accounting for both sides of the ball

 • The cumulative view shows how teams have performed throughout the season, with steeper upward slopes indicating elite play

QUARTERBACK STATS:

 • Total EPA: Expected Points Added - total offensive value generated across all plays

 • Passing Yards: Total passing yards thrown

 • Passing TDs: Total touchdown passes thrown

 • Completion %: Completion percentage (completions / attempts × 100)

 • Pass CPOE: Completion Percentage Over Expected - accuracy beyond what's expected based on throw difficulty

 • PACR: Pass Air Conversion Ratio - measures QB efficiency converting air yards to actual yards (Formula: Passing Yards / Air Yards). Higher PACR indicates more yards after catch.

 • Yards/Game: Average passing yards per game

 • Interceptions: Total interceptions thrown

RUNNING BACK STATS:

 • Rush EPA: Expected Points Added on rushing plays

 • Rushing Yards: Total rushing yards gained

 • Rushing TDs: Total rushing touchdowns

 • Yards/Carry: Average yards per rushing attempt

 • Rush Yards/Game: Average rushing yards per game

 • Receptions: Total receptions

 • Receiving Yards: Total receiving yards

 • Receiving TDs: Total receiving touchdowns

 • Rec Yards/Game: Average receiving yards per game

 • Target Share: Percentage of team's total targets

RECEIVER STATS:

 • Rec EPA: Expected Points Added on receptions

 • Receiving Yards: Total receiving yards gained

 • Receiving TDs: Total receiving touchdowns

 • Receptions: Total receptions

 • Yards/Reception: Average yards per reception

 • Rec Yards/Game: Average receiving yards per game

 • Catch %: Catch percentage (receptions / targets × 100)

 • WOPR: Weighted Opportunity Rating - combines targets and air yards to measure receiving opportunity

 • RACR: Receiver Air Conversion Ratio - receiving yards per air yard (measures efficiency converting targets to yards)

 • Target Share: Percentage of team's total targets

 • Air Yards %: Percentage of team's total air yards

All EPA stats are per play through the current week.
